
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `l2ping` baraye check kardane vasl boodan (connectivity) dastgah-ha az tarigh Bluetooth estefade mishavad. Yani mishe ba in dastoor, az vasl boodan ya naboodan Bluetooth devices motmaen shod.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `l2ping -c [tedad]`  --> 🔢  Ersale tedad moshakhas ping be device.
    🔹 `l2ping -i [taakhire zamani]` --> ⏳ Taakhire zamani bein har ping ra moshakhas mikonad (be soorate saniye).
    🔹 `l2ping -s [size packet]`  --> 📦  Size packet data ra moshakhas mikonad.
    🔹 `l2ping -t [Hadsaghar zaman ping]` --> ⏱️  Hadsaghar zaman ping baraie tamam shodan ping.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ l2ping AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF

    🔹 Check kardane vasl boodan device ba address Bluetooth AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF .

    $ l2ping -c 5 AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF

    🔹 Ersale 5 ta ping be device ba address Bluetooth AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF .

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ l2ping -c 3 00:11:22:33:44:55
    Ping: 00:11:22:33:44:55 from 00:00:00:00:00:00 (data size 44) ...
    0 bytes from 00:11:22:33:44:55 id 0 time 5.067ms
    Ping: 00:11:22:33:44:55 from 00:00:00:00:00:00 (data size 44) ...
    0 bytes from 00:11:22:33:44:55 id 1 time 7.342ms
    Ping: 00:11:22:33:44:55 from 00:00:00:00:00:00 (data size 44) ...
    0 bytes from 00:11:22:33:44:55 id 2 time 6.989ms
    3 transmitted, 3 received, 0% loss

    🔹 Ersale 3 ping be address Bluetooth 00:11:22:33:44:55 va namayesh etela'at vasl boodan.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `l2ping` command is used to check the connectivity of devices via Bluetooth. It allows you to verify if a Bluetooth device is reachable.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `l2ping -c [count]` --> 🔢 Send a specific number of pings to the device.
    🔹 `l2ping -i [interval]` --> ⏳ Set the time interval between pings (in seconds).
    🔹 `l2ping -s [packet size]` --> 📦 Set the size of the data packet.
    🔹 `l2ping -t [Timeout]` --> ⏱️ Set the timeout until the ping fails.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ l2ping AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF

    🔹 Check connectivity of the device with Bluetooth address AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF.

    $ l2ping -c 5 AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF

    🔹 Send 5 pings to the device with Bluetooth address AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ l2ping -c 3 00:11:22:33:44:55
    Ping: 00:11:22:33:44:55 from 00:00:00:00:00:00 (data size 44) ...
    0 bytes from 00:11:22:33:44:55 id 0 time 5.067ms
    Ping: 00:11:22:33:44:55 from 00:00:00:00:00:00 (data size 44) ...
    0 bytes from 00:11:22:33:44:55 id 1 time 7.342ms
    Ping: 00:11:22:33:44:55 from 00:00:00:00:00:00 (data size 44) ...
    0 bytes from 00:11:22:33:44:55 id 2 time 6.989ms
    3 transmitted, 3 received, 0% loss

    🔹 Sends 3 pings to the Bluetooth address 00:11:22:33:44:55 and displays the connectivity information.
